			Life Meter Help & FAQs
		%p
			Life Meter is a first-of-its-kind natural language platform that let's you easily track any health-related metrics or activities.
		%p
			Life Meter is designed to help you get the most out of life by making it easy to measure, control, and analyze the behaviors most important to your health and wellbeing. Read on to get the most out of your Life Meter!

		%h3
			A note on Beta-Testing
		%p
			First off, we're really excited about Life Meter and we really appreciate your help in making it better. Just a couple things to note before we begin...
		%p
			Life Meter is currently Beta. The term 'Beta' gets grossly over-used in software development, but in this case we really mean it. Life Meter is under active development. That means:
			%ol
				%li{ style: 'margin-bottom:1em;' }
					Things just may not work. That's kind of Beta-Testing 101.
				%li{ style: 'margin-bottom:1em;' }
					Features and functionality may change at any time. We'll try to communicate any changes before they happen, but we will be fixing critical bugs and incorporating your feedback continuously
				%li{ style: 'margin-bottom:1em;' }
					YOU MAY LOOSE ANY DATA YOU LOG DURING THE TEST. Some fixes, updates, and changes may require a hard-reset to the Life Meter database. We will try very hard not to permanently destroy data, but there's a good chance it could happen. Please don't use Life Meter for anything you really need or haven't backed up during the beta phase.
				%li{ style: 'margin-bottom:1em;' }
					For debugging and testing purposes, THE DATA YOU LOG MAY NOT BE PRIVATE. Please don't log sensitive personal data that you wouldn't want the developers of Life Meter to see. Once live, Life Meter will be secured over https and private, but engineers may need to access data to debug issues during the beta test. Please be mindful of this.

		%h3
			What can Life Meter do?
		%p
			In a nutshell, you can use Life Meter to track, report on, and analyze any vital stat that you care about. You can log and track information like your weight or pulse. You can track your calories or macronutrients. You can use Life Meter as a timer to log and track time you spend doing various activities. Life Meter will keep track of everything you report to it and give you useful reports andinsights into your data. You can even set targets for anything you track. Want to keep your caloric intake under 2000 calories per day? Just let Life Meter know, and it will let you know how many calories ou've eaten and how many you have left until your target.

